<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <title>Bonita OpenAPI Documentation</title>
    <link rel="icon" href="/images/favicon.png">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge" />
    <meta description="Bonita provides REST API’s to interact with the Runtime. Learn how to use them here">
    <meta name="keywords" content="REST, API, Bonita, BPM, OpenApi, Postman, Swagger, Documentation">
    <meta name="author" content="Bonitasoft">
    <meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8"/>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="/css/main.css">
</head>
<body>
<div class="header"><a class="bonita-logo" href="{{siteUrl}}"></a>
</div>

<div style="width: 50%; margin: auto">
    <h1>Bonita REST API Documentation</h1>
    <div style="text-align: center">
        <img src="/images/bonita-resources-doc.png" style="width:400px">
    </div>
    <h3>OpenAPI v3</h3>
    <p>
        Bonita provides an <a href="https://swagger.io/specification/">OpenAPI v3</a> specification for the REST APIs
        exposed by the platform.
    </p>
    <p>
        Bonita provide a REST API than can be accessed by any HTTP client, <code>rest</code> or <code>curl</code>,
        or the HTTP library which is part of most modern programming languages.
    </p>
    <p>
        If you are already using Java, have a look at the <a href="https://github.com/bonitasoft/bonita-java-client">Bonita
        java client</a> which allow you to build apps interacting with Bonita quickly and easily.<br/>
        If Java don’t work for you, you can use the Bonita HTTP API directly. The java client code is mostly generated
        based on the Bonita OpenAPI specification.
    </p>
    <h3>View the API references</h3>
    <ul>
        {{#each releases}}
            <li>Version <a href="{{../siteUrl}}/{{this}}/">{{this}}</a></li>
        {{/each}}
    </ul>

    <h3>Compatibility matrix</h3>
    <table class="compatibility-table">
        <thead>
        <tr>
            <th>Bonita version</th>
            <th class="rest-api-column">REST API versions</th>
        </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
        {{#each compatibility}}
            <tr>
                <td><b>{{this.bonita}}</b> ({{this.bonitaSemver}})</td>
                <td class="rest-api-column">
                    {{#each apiVersions}}
                        <a href="{{../siteUrl}}/{{this}}">{{this}}</a>
                    {{/each}}
                </td>
            </tr>
        {{/each}}
        </tbody>
    </table>

    <h3>Documentation archives</h3>
    <p>
        If you need to access to OpenAPI documentation not published on this site anymore,
        you can still download the zipped documentation from previous releases from Github repository <a
            href="https://github.com/bonitasoft/bonita-openapi/releases">bonita-openapi</a>
    </p>
</div>
{{#if ga_key}}
    <script async src="https://www.googletagmanager.com/gtag/js?id={{ga_key}}"></script>
    <script>function gtag() {
        dataLayer.push(arguments)
    };window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
    gtag('js', new Date());
    gtag('config', '{{ga_key}}')</script>
{{/if}}
{{#if watch}}
    <!-- Script for livereload -->
    <script>
        document.write('<script src="http://' + (location.host || 'localhost').split(':')[0] +
                ':{{liveReloadPort}}/livereload.js?snipver=1"></' + 'script>')
    </script>
{{/if}}
</body>
</html>
